{
  "title": "Instagram & Threads\nSecret Strategy",
  "subtitle": "Full Warmup, Growth & Monetization SOP",
  "output_filename": "SOPs/Instagram Threads Secret Strategy.pdf",
  "sections": [
    {
      "header": "Foreword: What This System Solves",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Most people fail because they post too early, post too much, and post without signals. Instagram does not push new accounts because content is \"good\". It pushes content when behavior looks human, consistent, and socially validated."
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Threads gives new pages reach without history. Instagram rewards pages that already look wanted. This SOP uses Threads to manufacture demand first, then uses Instagram to amplify it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Platform Roles & Traffic Logic",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "You are not \"growing on two platforms\". You are running one system with two tools."
        },
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Threads — Used To"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Trigger comments",
                "Start conversations",
                "Test narratives",
                "Send people to your IG profile"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Threads posts should make someone think: \"Who is this girl?\""
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Instagram — Used To"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Visually lock the persona",
                "Build trust",
                "Convert attention into clicks and money"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Instagram posts should make someone think: \"I've seen her before — she's real.\""
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Warmup Phase: Exactly What to Do",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Duration: 21-28 days. Goal: Teach Instagram your account is human, local, and valuable. This phase is boring on purpose. If you rush this, everything after breaks."
        },
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "What to POST"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "2-3 carousels per week (face-focused, lifestyle, clean, SFW)",
                "2-3 stories per week (selfies, food, random daily stuff)",
                "No questions, no CTA, no horny captions",
                "No links, no selling"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "What to DO Daily"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Scroll for 15-30 minutes",
                "Like posts from English-speaking creators",
                "Comment occasionally (normal comments)",
                "Follow accounts slowly (5-10/day max)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "What NOT to Do"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "No Reels",
                "No Threads",
                "No link in bio",
                "No horny captions",
                "No links",
                "No selling"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "panel",
              "title": "Critical Warning",
              "content": "If you rush the warmup, everything after breaks. There are no shortcuts.",
              "border": "#FF3131"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Threads Phase 1: How to Post & Reply",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Goal: Force comments and profile visits. Start after warmup, or last 7 days of warmup if engagement is stable."
        },
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Posting Rules"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "1 post per day",
                "Always text-based",
                "Optional photo (cute, casual, not polished)",
                "Light comparison or validation bait"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Post Angles to Use"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "\"Does anyone even like ___ girls?\"",
                "\"Am I wrong for wanting ___?\"",
                "\"My parents hate ___ about me\"",
                "\"Be honest, does this look bad?\""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Reply Hijacking"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Find Threads posted 2-4 hours ago",
                "Reply with text + selfie",
                "Ask follow-up questions",
                "Be slightly unsure — keep them talking"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "good_example",
              "content": "\"Really? I always thought it made me look weird\""
            },
            {
              "type": "bad_example",
              "content": "\"aww ty\""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "You are making people reassure her, argue, and explain things to her. You are always asking for validation or opinion."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Threads Phase 2: Scaling & Testing",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Goal: Turn Threads into a traffic engine. Phase 2 starts when posts get comments consistently, profile visits increase, and IG followers rise without Reels."
        },
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Posting"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "3-4 posts per day",
                "Same formats, same angles",
                "Slight wording changes",
                "Do NOT rotate just to rotate"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "If Something Works"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Repeat it",
                "Slightly change phrasing",
                "Slightly change context"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "If something dies: drop it and move on."
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Content Expansion (Still SFW)"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "More confident",
                "Slightly flirtier text",
                "Glow-up narratives"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Real-Time Rebrands (Allowed)"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Hair color change",
                "Accessories (glasses, eyepatch)",
                "Story-based changes (glow-up narrative)"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "bad_example",
              "content": "New face\nNew body\nCompletely different model"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Instagram Reels: Exact Launch Process",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "When to Start"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Warmup done",
                "Threads active",
                "Comments flowing",
                "Viral Thread = boost, not requirement"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "First Reels"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "High-quality, SFW, scroll-stopping",
                "Parent or lifestyle works well",
                "1 quality Reel per day",
                "More only if quality stays high"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "After Posting"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Stay active and reply to comments",
                "Keep Threads running for 2-3 weeks"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "If Reels Flop"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Keep posting",
                "Change format",
                "Do NOT stop"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Instagram Content Execution",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Stories"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Daily if possible",
                "Lifestyle and personality",
                "No links before 3 weeks"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Carousels"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Never upload raw AI images",
                "Use Photoshop / Photopea",
                "Add approximately 2% grain"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Reels"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Quality over quantity",
                "Replicate first viral format",
                "Use trial reels to test risky ideas"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Trial Reels"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Reuse clips",
                "Change text and order",
                "Fully experimental"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Geo Targeting & Distribution Control",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Target"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "English-speaking countries",
                "USA priority",
                "EU acceptable"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Signaling"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "USA city locations",
                "American music",
                "Flag emojis in moderation"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Geo Blocking (LAST RESORT)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Geo blocking is not a default strategy. It is an emergency correction tool used when Instagram repeatedly pushes content to the wrong audience."
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Use Instagram native age restriction by country",
                "Go to Settings → Business Tools → Minimum Age",
                "Set highest age for countries to limit",
                "Do not use on brand-new accounts",
                "Continue posting USA-targeted content while active"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "header": "Final Rules & Failure Recovery",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "two_column",
          "left": [
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Do NOT"
            },
            {
              "type": "bullets",
              "items": [
                "Post Reels early",
                "Switch models",
                "Overpost trash",
                "Add links early"
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "subheader",
              "content": "Adaptation Rule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "If something does not work after a couple weeks, change it."
            }
          ],
          "right": [
            {
              "type": "panel",
              "title": "Core Rule",
              "content": "Patience beats aggression.\nThis strategy fails when you stop learning and quit.",
              "border": "#39FF14"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "summary_points": [
    "Threads manufactures demand first, then Instagram amplifies it",
    "The warmup phase (21-28 days) is mandatory and boring on purpose",
    "Threads posts should force comments, arguments, and profile visits",
    "Reels launch only after Threads proves engagement is stable",
    "Never upload raw AI images — always edit for realism",
    "Geo targeting prioritizes USA/English-speaking audiences",
    "Patience beats aggression — this strategy fails when you quit",
    "Treat every post as data — repeat what works, drop what does not"
  ]
}